posts.body: If 8chan gets permanently shoah'd, I think going out on a UT stream wouldn't be so bad

>Posting on a post-chanocalyptic board. Feels breddy comfy.
We are moving closer and closer to the Promised Chan, feels good man

>1324
That's just p2p connections correct? How would you check unique users on each board?

Strike at the appendages we have reaching into normalfag net all you like, the heart of 8chan will always live on.
==GG, NO RE==

>>536dc46f-555a-422d-8181-c3570d1aa2c4
it's an obtuse way of doing it but clicking the mute button on a post will show you that user's certificate. You could scan an entire thread **if you were autistic** to see if someone is just replying to them self. I suppose you could even track a user's posts through different threads and boards if they don't refresh their certificate **if you were really autistic**

posts.body:
>>ddf7cc95-5777-4113-80e3-8a6fc245e1ce
Anyone autistic enough to stream UT yearly is probably autistic enough to know where the bunkers are. 

>>5ee62fe4-7055-4d04-af94-bb16b901c2b5
>8chan could be confirmed dead within a week
>Thassil could be MIA within a week, with no one knowing where he's gone
I just hope enough anons migrated somewhere they can still be reached in time for the stream

>>2a072e8c-fadb-4eb6-85cc-5729f8498dc7
I'm impressed with your autism. Doing good work, anon

>>b53eb99e-35d9-4779-b85e-8c3c5ec9b0fb
Many anons are all still holed up in their bunkers waiting for 8chan to come back online. Out of all the bunkers, this one probably is the most viable to migrate to. If 8chan is removed/rendered unusable for a long enough time, I think you could see the former userbase start making there way here. Otherwise this will probably remain as just one of the more populated bunkers.
